manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MSI is the most trusted name in gaming and eSports. We’ve dedicated countless hours and committed numerous resources to support the world’s most aspiring and best gamers and use their knowledge and expertise in our products in return. MSI integrated all gamer’s aspirational functions in its gaming rigs and pushing the performance beyond limits. MSI GAMING X Graphics Cards with TWIN FROZR 7 PLAY HARD, STAY SILENT The latest iteration of MSI’s iconic dual-fan GAMING series pushes the limits of performance, efficiency, and aesthetics once again. Sustain incredible boost performance from GeForce GTX core with the TWIN FROZR 7 cooling system. Keep temperatures under control with the aerodynamic heatsink and efficient high-airflow fans, all clad between a metal backplate and blacked-out shroud.

TURING SHADERS Featuring concurrent execution of floating point and integer operations, adaptive shading technology, and a new unified memory architecture with twice the cache of its predecessor, NVIDIA Turing shaders enable awesome performance increases on today’s games. AWESOME PERFORMANCE Get game ready with performance that rivals the GeForce GTX 1070 on the latest games with the GeForce GTX 1660 Ti and 1660. GEFORCE EXPERIENCE Capture and share videos, screenshots, and livestreams with friends. Keep your GeForce drivers up to date. And optimize your game settings. GeForce Experience lets you do it all. It’s the essential companion to your GeForce graphics card.

TORX Fan 3.0 Alternating dispersion and traditional fan blades push the limits of thermal performance and low-noise efficiency. Dispersion fan blades move air with increased static pressure. Traditional fan blades with new trims stabilize turbulence and create focused airflow. Backplate Covering the back of the fully custom PCB is a brushed metal reinforcing backplate for a clean and sharp aesthetic. Afterburner Take full control with MSI Afterburner featuring OC Scanner. Overclock your graphics card and monitor your system’s key metrics in real-time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing little monster
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Was blown away with this little monster. It can easily play 1440p but is amazing with 1080p. Stays pretty damn cool and I was so impressed by that. Playing Witcher, b5 at high setting and saying under 58c.. this was for a customer but even my 2080 ti doesn’t stay that cool with those games. I would def recommend this card to anyone. For 250?!! This is a steal imo. I had zero problems running anything B5,the Witcher , final Fantasy,sea of thrieves, gtfo, the forest, and other games. If I knew about the card sooner I would of got this instead of my 2080 ti and save money. Lol but for real great card for the money. Oh the rgb is dope af too

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good GPU to wait out the storm.
reviews.reviewText: As of writing this review, there is a Graphics Card shortage due to CoVid-19, Silicon Shortage, Scalpers, and Bitcoin Miners. While this card WAS sold well above MSRP, $551 compared to my firstborn child was a no brainer. This graphics card curbstomps the old Radeon Pro 555 in my old 2017 iMac, and runs Warzone on 100+ frames, on a 1080p 144hz monitor. Minecraft with Sildur’s Extreme Shaders will run at about 80-90fps on 1090p 144hz. Attila: Total War, and Rome: 2 Total war run very well on ultra settings, though WILL significantly drop when you zoom in to where the fighting is thickest (probably due to all of the blood effects and bodies it is rendering), but overall allows a very good experience.The fans are very quiet on automatic (using MSI afterburner), and hardly noticeable. As an entry level PC gamer with my very first PC build, I would say this is a good card to wait out the shortage with. If you can snag this for about $500-$550, then by all means buy it, as it is a hell of a lot better than paying $1500 for a RTX 2060.Overall the GTX 1660 was a very good upgrade for me, and I hope to grind out many more hours on my favorite games with this beauty.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2019
reviews.reviewText: I can't really speak to gaming as I'm not a gamer but not being the highest powered or most expensive card I went 4 stars on general principals. This went into an older Intel DQ77MK motherboard with a Gen 4 core I7 processor, raided SSDs for the OS and raided mechanical drives for data. It replaces a Nvidia GTX 650.This card barely fits the motherboard but it did fit.I had to change the SATA cable for the 5th connector from straight to 90 degrees at the mother board because the end of the card falls over the connector. There will be no replacing of motherboard memory without taking the card out as the card sits flush against end of the memory sockets with them locked in, no room to swivel the locks.I also replaced the power supply, as this card requires an 8 pin VGA connector and the old PS only had a 6 pin. The old PS has quite a few miles on it and the odds are that electrolytic capacitors will eventually become problematic, so I didn't mind springing for a new supply.The change in performance is very noticeable, streaming video is smoother, pages and photos pop faster, the fans are nicely quiet. Based on the Passmark comparisons with more expensive cards, I would agree with other comments that this card may be one of the best at Bang for the Buck.It has only been in play a short time but I am very happy with the purchase

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing Performance. Satisfied with my upgrade choice
reviews.reviewText: After saving up and holding out for the past two years I finally saved enough to upgrade from a potato PC to a new rig.My new build features this GTX 1660 and a Ryzen 2600 and a B450 motherboard.I'm able to play all my games at 60+ FPS on ultra settings with my 1080p monitor. Turning down graphics to medium/high with flashy graphics off I'm able to hit 100+ FPS in some games. I'm fine with 60FPS ultra because I currently do not have a good monitor. So far I am very satisfied with this graphics card. it looks amazing with a black/gray color design. The RGB is a little extra and I really do like the backplate for this card. This is one of the pricer GTX 1660 but MSI has proven to be worth the extra $20 with their design and cooling. Hopefully I do not have any issues to report. For now this is definitely a nice upgrade from my old GTX 750 Ti.I saw no design to go for a RTX 2060 because I did not see myself using the Ray Tracing feature. If you're looking to upgrade from a old video card this is definitely worth considering.PS - If you're playing APEX LEGENDS this card will handle it without a problem :)

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Hope to see more from this company!
reviews.reviewText: Long story made short, I already have one of these GPUs and I’m making a second pc for my girlfriend. Graphics card is wonderful and works great unfortunately due to scalpers some prices have risen. Techzone Tips is doing a wonderful job at keeping these on the more affordable side. They were fast and courteous enough to write me a hand written letter. My largest issue come with the fact that they required an “adult” (age 21 or older) to sign for approval of the package. Seeing as I am only 19 I had issues getting the package for legal issue. Had my dad help me out and otherwise was fine. In summary:1. Great product highly recommend for mid-high end gaming.2. Great company in progress and I hope to see their business become a great company.3.New company still in the works of ironing things out so although I had an issue acquiring the package just a small hump to overcome.

reviews.reviewerName: Salvador Alejandro Casarez MezaSalvador Alejandro Casarez Meza
reviews.reviewText: Es una tarjeta grafica bastante buena para los juegos actuales, corre la mayoría de juegos en calidad alta (Fornite, Apex y Warzone, etc) pero yo recomendaría ponerlos en calidad media para tener mejor rendimiento, ya que no es tan poderosa como las rtx, pero es buena opción si quieres iniciar en el pc gaming.No se me ha calentado nunca y los ventiladores se encienden automáticamente cuando se requieren, así que no es un gasto de energía constante.El instructivo te dice todo lo que debes de saber para ensamblar, y también viene con un cómic que te muestra como hacerlo si es que solo la quieres ensamblar y no leer todo lo técnico.No he tenido problemas desde que me llego hace ya 4 meses. Solo que el precio es alto si llegara a bajar es bastante recomendable.
Very good product and best thing about it is that it’s a Taiwan country made.

Exclusivo producto y de muy buena calidad, aunque si tienen un poco más de presupuesto les recomendaría la 1660 super.Pero esta no deja de ser una excelente opción la eh probado con juegos triple A y competitivos y me ah dejado muy sorprendido con los resultados
